author: Tomrulz25
title: 6444 Outback airstrip
review: What a cool little set. This is an ideal lego product; quick easy build, excellent detail and plenty of accesories for maximum playibility. At the release it was a very reasonable price. These two good reviews dont do it enough justice. A+

author: A_Brickset_user
title: I loved this set so much.
review:
This is officially my all time favorite LEGO set. I got it when I was in 3rd grade, I believe age 7-8. It took a week to come in the mail and I was so happy when it came. I remember looking forward to it all the time at school that week.

Great set to any city.

author: benners30
title: ausie airstip
review:
this set is designed mainly on a small airstip in the middle of the desert in australia. this set has a small 4 studs wide aircraft, 3 figs, a windmill, a shack and tons of rare accesories. pros/cons time!

airplane:
pros:
yellow
2 prop engines 
4 wide 
high wings
cool tail design
cons:
could be about 2 studs longer

airport:
pros:
looks very rustic
has a awesome windmill
cool sand baseplate
cons:
could use a touch more detail.

accesories/figs:
pros:
3 figs
radio block
boom box
lots of cool lil brushes and pieces
cons:
should have had a ladder for the plane

great set
